    "AlertId": "114904",
    "Headline": "EXTENDED: Bus Substitution Between Pulaski and 54th/Cermak Stations",
    "ShortDescription": "EXTENDED: Shuttle buses continue to replace Pink Line service between Pulaski and 54th/Cermak due to unforeseen utility issues during planned weekend work.",
    "FullDescription": {
      "#cdata-section": "<p><strong>How does this affect my trip?</strong><br />\r\nShuttle buses continue to replace rail service between Pulaski and 54th/Cermak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trains will operate between Pulaski and the Loop, every 15 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alternate service through the affected area is available on the #21 Cermak bus route during the normal hours of operation (normal bus fares apply).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allow extra travel time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why is service being changed?</strong><br />\r\nWe are performing railroad grade crossing maintenance at Cicero Avenue to ensure that trains continue to operate safely along the Pink Line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Modified train service will remain in effect through Monday, until completion, while we work to restore normal service after unforeseen utility issues encountered over the weekend.</p>\r\n"
    },
